olive oil
2 potato
1 stalk celery
1 packet Sweet Soy Seasoning
1 packet chicken breast
1 packet sweet chilli sauce
1 bag Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 packet Japanese Dressing
drizzle vinegar (rice wine or white wine)
1 packet mayonnaise

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Cut potato into fries, then place on a lined oven tray.
• Season with salt and drizzle with olive oil. Toss to coat, spread out evenly, then bake until tender, 20-25 minutes.

Little cooks: Kids can help toss the fries.

• Meanwhile, thinly slice celery.
• Place your hand flat on top of chicken breast and slice through horizontally to make two thin steaks.

• In a medium bowl, combine sweet soy seasoning and a drizzle of olive oil. Add chicken and turn to coat.

• Heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook chicken until cooked through, 3-5 minutes each side.
• Remove pan from heat, add sweet chilli sauce and turn chicken to coat.
TIP: Chicken is cooked through when it's no longer pink inside.

• In a second medium bowl, combine shredded cabbage mix, celery, Japanese dressing and a drizzle of vinegar. Season to taste.

Little cooks: Help combine the ingredients for the slaw!

• Slice the chicken.
• Divide fries, celery slaw and sweet chilli-glazed chicken between plates.
• Serve with mayonnaise. Enjoy!